------------------------------------ COUNT WORS IN STRING--------------------------------------

import java.util.* ;
import java.io.*; 
import java.util.Scanner;
class Solution {
	
    static int  countWords(String input) {

        String arr[] = input.trim().split("\\s+");
        return arr.length;
    }
    
	public static void main(String args[]) {
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String input = sc.nextLine();
        int output = countWords(input);
        System.out.println(output);
		
	}
}
Sample Input 1:
Coding Ninjas!
Sample Output 1:
2

For a given input string(str), find and return the total number of words present in it.
It is assumed that two words will have only a single space in between. Also, there wouldn't 
be any leading and trailing spaces in the given input string.


----------------------FIND LENGTH OF LAST WORD IN STRING ------------------------------------------

class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLastWord(String s) {

    int i = s.length() - 1;
    int count = 0;
    
    while(i >= 0 && s.charAt(i) == ' '){
        i--;
    }

    while(i >= 0 && s.charAt(i)!= ' '){
        count++;
        i--;
    }
        return count;
    }
}

Input: s = "Hello World"
Output: 5
Explanation: The last word is "World" with length 5.

Given a string s consisting of words and spaces, return the length of the last word in the string.
A word is a maximal substring consisting of non-space characters only.
